													$('jt_map_enlarge').show();">Smaller map</a><a id=jt_map_street_zoom href=javascript:void(0); onclick=map.setZoom(15);>Zoom to Street</a><br><br><div id=jt_map style="width: 99%; height: 200px; border: 1px solid black;"></div></div></div></div><div id=jt_job_summary><p><em>This is not an entry-level position.</em></p><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><th>Job ID:</th><td>7431983</td></tr><tr><th>Position Title:</th><td>Systems/Software Engr VI</td></tr><tr><th>Min Education:</th><td>H.S. Diploma/Equivalent</td></tr><tr><th>Industry:</th><td>Computer Software</td></tr></table></td><td><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><th>Posted:</th><td>December 5, 2010</td></tr><tr><th>Job Function:</th><td>Information Technology</td></tr><tr><th>Job Type:</th><td>Full-Time</td></tr><tr><th>Salary:</th><td>Yearly Salary)</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></div><div id=jt_job_contact><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><th>Apply URL:</th><td><a href="http://ars2.equest.com/?response_id=1ede208cb523975dd1bee44885213798">http://ars2.equest.com/?response_id=1ede208cb52397...</a></td></tr></table></td><td> &nbsp; </td></tr></table></div><div id=jt_job_description> HP is a leading global provider of products, technologies, solutions and services to consumers and business. The company's offerings span IT infrastructure, personal computing and access devices, global services, and imaging and printing. Our $4 billion annual R&D investment fuels the invention of products, solutions and new technologies so we can better serve customers and enter new markets. We invent, engineer and deliver technology solutions that drive business value, create social value and improve the lives of our customers. &nbsp; HP Networking Software/Firmware Engineers play lead roles in multi-discipline teams working on new networking products and solutions. This includes active involvement in product feature definition, hardware feature requirements, hardware bring-up, SW development and test, customer documentation, and on-going product support. Projects typically involve coordination with internal and external development teams, often in other geographies. Enabling others is as important as personal contribution.<br> &nbsp;<br> We are seeking talented, motivated software professionals with a background in Ethernet router/switch software/firmware development. Job responsibilities include all phases of the software lifecycle model. Successful candidates must possess a passion for delivering high quality supportable software that effectively meets customer requirements. They must also be comfortable working in a formal software development environment where rigorous focus on and adherence to process are critical.<br> &nbsp;<br> This particular position primarily involves development of L2/L3 router/switch features for the HP Networking family of wired switch products. &nbsp;<br> &nbsp;<br><br> &nbsp; <span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold"> Musts<br><ul style="LIST-STYLE-TYPE: disc"><li>BS in CS/CE or equivalent combination of education and experience.</li><li>Basic knowledge of cpu architecture, cache, asics, i/o devices memory, data storage</li><li>Proficiency in C, C++ and object-oriented architecture, design and coding</li><li>Proficiency in debugging technologies and approaches including source-level debuggers and code analysis techniques</li><li>Strong software design skills including a detailed understanding of SW concepts and knowledge of modeling techniques and technologies such as UML</li><li>Strong understanding of data structures</li><li>Strong understanding of system-level design principles</li><li>Basic understanding of OS concepts, algorithms and operation</li><li>Experience with SW version control and defect tracking</li><li>Basic understanding of sw test methodologies (unit, integration, system, etc)</li><li>Experience in TCP/IP, IPv4 and IPv6 Networking protocols (routing, security, redundancy) and knowledge of Switch ASIC architectures/drivers.</li><li>Strong interpersonal, teamwork and communications skills.</li><li>Ability to learn quickly and work independently with minimal supervision.</li><li>Unix/Linux/Windows experience</li><li><span style="font-family:MS Shell Dlg 2;font-size:x-small"><span style="font-family:MS Shell Dlg 2;font-size:x-small">Strong understanding and demonstrated ability to create and conduct module and/or unit tests</span></span></li></ul> &nbsp;<br> Desired<br> MS or advanced degree in CS/CE or equivalent combination of education and experience.<br></span><img src="http://ars2.equest.com/?response_id=1ede208cb523975dd1bee44885213798&amp;view" alt=" " width=1 height=1></div><a id=jt_return_to_search_2 class=jt_return_to_search href="/c2/search.cfm?site%5Fid=1#job7431983">&laquo;&nbsp;Return to Results</a></div></td></tr></table><iframe src="/c/includes/jvi.cfm?site_id=1&job=7431983" style=display:none;width:1px;height:1px;></iframe></div></td></tr></table></div><div id=jt_footer> Copyright &copy; 2007 JobTarget, All Rights Reserved.<br><a href=http://www.jobtargetjobfinder.com>Job Seeker Services</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp; <a href=http://www.jobtarget.com/corp/products-services/job-board-solutions/ >Job Board Services</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp; <a href=http://www.jobtargetoneclick.com>Recruiting Services</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp; <a href=/c2/tou.cfm>Terms of Usage</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp; <a href=http://www.jobtarget.com/corp/privacy-policy/ >Privacy Policy</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp; <a href=http://www.jobtarget.com/corp/company/company-overview/ >About JobTarget</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp; <a href="/c2/support.cfm?site_id=1">Contact JobTarget</a></div></body></html><div id=overDiv style="position: absolute; display: none; z-index: 1000;"></div>

