ervers and Networking Business Unit. We are responsible for delivering products and solutions targeted at enabling virtualization on HP industry standard server platforms. We are looking for candidates who are interested in being part of an engineering team delivering infrastructure management for virtualized platforms. We expect our systems/software engineers to engage with HP partners, other HP teams and participate in the full software lifecycle from investigation, requirements, design, development, qualification and release.<br> &nbsp;<br><b>Job description </b> The Sr. Systems/Software Engineer will be responsible for: - Designing and developing software products in a timely manner adhering to high quality standards<br> - Working with Software Testing / QA organizations to achieve quality requirements<br> - Troubleshooting / Debugging product issues - Collaborating with cross functional and remote project team members for successful project completion<br> - Working with external partners as needed<br> &nbsp;<br> Applies developed subject matter knowledge to solve common and complex business issues within established guidelines and recommends appropriate alternatives. &nbsp;Works on problems/projects of diverse complexity and scope. &nbsp;Exercises independent judgment within generally defined policies and practices to identify and select a solution. &nbsp;May act as a team or project leader providing direction to team activities and facilitates information validation and team decision-making process. &nbsp;Ability to handle most unique situations. &nbsp;May seek advice in order to make decisions on complex business issues. <p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><strong>Education</strong></p><p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">Bachelor&#39;s (undergraduate) or Master&#39;s (graduate) in Computer Science/Engineering or equivalent.</p><p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">&nbsp;</p><p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><strong>Experience and knowledge</strong></p><ul><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Bachelor&#39;s or Master&#39;s degree in computer Science/Engineering or equivalent experience and a minimum of 8 plus years related experience.</span></span></li><li><span style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Demonstrated success developing a customer facing software product with experience of the complete software lifecycle.</span></span></span><br></li><li><span style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Experience with industry standard x86-based virtualization</span></span></span><br></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Experience with virtualization management product development</span></span></li><li><span style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Experience with x86 based in-band and out-of-band server management product</span></span></span><br></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Experience debugging / troubleshooting large, complex and interdependent software</span></span></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Experience with Microsoft software development tools and</span></span></li></ul><p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><strong>Core skills</strong></p><p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">&nbsp;</p><ul><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Object oriented design, implementation and test</span></span></li><li><span style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Strong software development and debugging</span></span></span><br></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Ability to collaborate and work in a team environment</span></span></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Ability to coordinate and collaborate with multiple HP internal teams and with external partners for timely completion of</span></span></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Analytical skills to research technical issues, troubleshoot complex systems and to deliver right</span></span></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Ability to multitask on a variety of software development lifecycle activities</span></span></li><li><span style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Strong English verbal and written communication skills</span></span></span><br></li></ul><p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">&nbsp;</p><p style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><strong>Technology Specialties</strong></p><ul><li><span style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">x86-based industry standard server architecture and platform management</span></span></span><br></li><li><span style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Strong knowledge of object oriented design, data modeling and common design patterns</span></span></span><br></li><li><span style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Strong distributed design and implementation</span></span></span><br></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Knowledge of Windows Server Operating Systems, Windows Internals and a working knowledge of the NT Kernel device</span></span></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">C# or C/C++ programming skills</span></span></li><li><span style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Experience with XML general schema</span></span></span><br></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Experience with Microsoft script technologies, including</span></span></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Industry experience with Microsoft development technologies, including .NET 3.5 (WCF, LINQ, WPF) and</span></span></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">General knowledge of virtualization concepts (highly desirable, but not required</span></span></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Working knowledge of Microsoft System Center products (SCOM, SCCM, SCVMM) (highly desirable, but not required</span></span></li><li><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Knowledge of systems management using WBEM and SNMP (desirable, but not required)</span></span></li><li><span style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: x-small"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Knowledge of RESTful web services (desirable, but not required)</span></span></span><br></li></ul><img src="http://ars2.equest.com/?response_id=eb47ce751528242d808a6f49adb11a8f&amp;view" alt=" " width=1 height=1></div><a id=jt_return_to_search_2 class=jt_return_to_search href="/c2/search.cfm?site%5Fid=1#job7247673">&laquo;&nbsp;Return to Results</a></div></td></tr></table><iframe src="/c/includes/jvi.cfm?site_id=1&job=7247673" style=display:none;width:1px;height:1px;></iframe></div></td></tr></table></div><div id=jt_footer> Copyright &copy; 2007 JobTarget, All Rights Reserved.<br><a href=http://www.jobtargetjobf