blEmploymentTypeKey class=bodybold>Employment type</span></td><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblEmploymentType class=body>Full Time</span></td></tr><tr><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblEducationKey class=bodybold>Education</span></td><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblEducation class=body>Not Specified</span></td></tr><tr><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblYearExperienceKey class=bodybold>Year Experience</span></td><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblYearExperience class=body>3 - 4 Years of Practical Experience</span></td></tr><tr><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblTravelKey class=bodybold>Travel</span></td><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblTravel class=body>Not Specified</span></td></tr><tr><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblCreateDateKey class=bodybold>Published on</span></td><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblCreateDate class=body>11/22/2010</span></td></tr></table><table width=385 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=10 valign=top><tr><td class=headerJobDetails><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblDescriptionKey>Description</span><br><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblDescription class=body>Systems Integration Analyst - Augusta, ME<br>$50K - $60K Base<br><br>Our client is a fast-growing company providing network solutions to utilities worldwide. They use advanced wireless networking technologies to help bring utility companies into the future. Our client is currently hiring a Systems Integration Analyst who will report to the Director of Systems Integration. The Systems Integration Analyst will be responsible for providing professional services as a key member of the solution delivery team.<br><br>ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS <br>? Installs and configures client software<br>? Troubleshoots and resolves system issues in customer environments<br>? Perform informal training to customer?s user groups on use and maintenance of software<br>? Participates on project teams deploying client software and other IT components. In most cases, the software implementation will be part of a larger technology deployment involving large scale (>1Million devices) networks<br>? Support the overall Project Director\Manager\ System Integration Lead as needed in project management activities<br>? Contribute to business process analysis and design, deployment planning and execution, and training development and delivery activities<br>? Interface with internal and client team members to complete project activities and required deliverables<br>? Develop expertise related to the utility industry and the client solutiondf-tc</span><br><br><br><br><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblExperienceKey>Experience/Skills</span><br><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblExperience class=body>POSITION REQUIREMENTS <br>? 5+ years hands on experience with complex systems<br>? Attention to technical detail<br>? Strong troubleshooting skills and a tenacious approach to issue resolution.<br>? Bachelor?s degree in engineering, computer science or related discipline<br>? Experience in the Utility, Smart Grid or Energy Management field is a plus<br>? Capable of communicating effectively to both business and technical resources<br>? Ability to excel in a dynamic, high growth environment<br>? Broad working knowledge of enterprise systems technology including:<br><br>*Databases - Oracle, MySQL<br><br>*Applications Development plaftorm s &#8208; Java,XML,<br><br>*Networking - Enterprise Security, Firewalls,TCP/IP<br><br><br>? Competency with Word, Excel, Powerpoint, Sharepoint, MS project and similar business tools<br>? Must be able to travel up to 75% of the time<br><br>PERSONAL ATTRIBUTES <br>Excellent verbal and written communications and interpersonal skills<br>Able to work independently with minimal supervision and self initiate diagnosis<br>Able to utilize problem solving methodologies while in the field independently<br><br>COMPENSATION<br>? $50K - $60K Base (DOE)<br>? Strong benefits plan and vacation package<br><br>TO APPLY<br>If you are interested in learning more about this great opportunity please send an updated resume to Craig at craig.macdonald@adeccona.com</span><br></td></tr></table><!-- google_ad_section_end --></td></tr><tr id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_trBottom><td valign=middle align=center height=50><input type=image name=ctl00$ctl00$contentMaster$content$btnApplyJobBottom id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_btnApplyJobBottom title="Apply to this job" src=/App_Themes/PublicSite/Images/btn_applynow_off.jpg onclick="location.href = 'http://www.tech-centric.net/Candidate/ApplyJob.aspx?JobID=733562'; return false;" onmouseover="this.src = '/App_Themes/PublicSite/Images/btn_applynow_on.jpg'" onmouseout="this.src = '/App_Themes/PublicSite/Images/btn_applynow_off.jpg'" border=0></td></tr></table></div></td><!--end center col--><!--begin right col--><td align=right valign=top width=120><table width=120 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td valign=middle><div id=tooltop><table width=120 height=27 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td><div align=center><img id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_Tools1_imgToolsTitle title=Tools src=/App_Themes/PublicSite/Images/title_tools.jpg height=16 width=39 border=0></div></td></tr></table></div></td></tr><tr><td><div id=toolbox><table width=120 height=254 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td align=center><a id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_Tools1_hhlCreateResume title="Tech Computer IT Technology Resume" href=/Candidate/Resume.aspx style=display:inline-block;><img title="Tech Computer IT Technology Resume" onmouseover="this.src = '/App_Themes/PublicSite/Images/btn_createres_on.jpg'" onmouseout="this.src = '/App_Themes/PublicSite/Images/btn_createres_off.jpg'" src=/App_Themes/PublicSite/Images/btn_createres_off.jpg border=0></a></td></tr><tr><td align=center><a id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_Tools1_hhlJobAge