tl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblEmploymentTypeKey class=bodybold>Employment type</span></td><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblEmploymentType class=body>Full Time</span></td></tr><tr><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblEducationKey class=bodybold>Education</span></td><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblEducation class=body>Not Specified</span></td></tr><tr><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblYearExperienceKey class=bodybold>Year Experience</span></td><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblYearExperience class=body>4 - 5 Years of Practical Experience</span></td></tr><tr><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblTravelKey class=bodybold>Travel</span></td><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblTravel class=body>Not Specified</span></td></tr><tr><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblCreateDateKey class=bodybold>Published on</span></td><td><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblCreateDate class=body>11/22/2010</span></td></tr></table><table width=385 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=10 valign=top><tr><td class=headerJobDetails><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblDescriptionKey>Description</span><br><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblDescription class=body>Ajilon Consulting is a global provider of IT solutions with 40 years of experience and offices throughout North America, Europe, and Australia. We support clients' immediate and long-term business needs by delivering a wide array of consultative IT services and by providing contingent consultants on an individual or group staffing basis. Our contingent consultants possess IT skills that supplement internal client resources during workload peaks, fill critical areas of expertise, and staff mission critical projects. <br>With our parent company Adecco, we have a wide presence in North America and globally with more than 6,600 offices in 70 countries worldwide. Together we employ more than 700,000 associates on-assignment supporting over 150,000 clients. <br><br>.NET Developer<br><br>Researches, designs, develops, and/or modifies enterprise-wide systems and/or applications software. Involved in planning of system and development deployment as well as responsible for meeting software compliance standards. Evaluates interface between hardware and software, operational requirements, and characteristics of overall system. Documents testing and maintenance of system corrections.<br><br>The position is located in Baltimore, on the west side of town near 695, Route 26, and Security Blvd.. We are responsible for providing a full range of IT integration services and supporting a multi-platform computing environment, including: information systems modernization initiatives, software engineering, project management, infrastructure services, data warehousing, database administration, research, planning, security, federal enterprise architecture initiatives, research and all levels of Internet, Intranet and Web portal initiatives and migrating legacy architecture to web-based platforms. All employees must be able to pass a Federal Suitability Check for a position of public trust.<br><br>The selected candidate is responsible for design, development, requirements gathering and analysis, to include business process analysis and modeling, usability, and Section 508 compliance. He/she works with technical oversight and is regarded as a senior-level developer. <br><br>Performs the following job duties:<br><br>* Plans and executes requirements analysis, business process modeling, usability and 508 compliance for development projects<br><br>* Provides information technology recommendations and solutions in support of customer requirements<br><br>*Applies industry best-practices and regarding emerging technologies, risk mitigation, and continuity planning<br><br>* Plans and conducts tests, and Ensures accurate documentation of technical specifications<br><br>* Tracking and maintaining all records and metric, reports the project's progress to management. <br>Skills Requirements: <br>Experience in enterprise web application development and direct working experience in an application development capacity<br><br>Experience in Data Warehousing - Dimensional Modeling, ETL, OLAP and Report Development<br><br>Demonstrated proficiency in Microsoft SharePoint 2007 <br><br>Demonstrated proficiency in .NET development, C#, ASP.NET, VB.NET, ADO.NET, VB, XML, XSLT, XHTML Mastery<br><br>Demonstrated proficiency in VB Script, JavaScript, CSS, AJAX, SQL <br><br>Demonstrated proficiency in ASP.NET Concepts, Control Proficiency, Page life Cycle, HttpHandler, HttpHandlerFactory and HttpModule Proficiency <br><br>Demonstrated proficiency in ADO.NET Fundamentals (DataTable, DataSet, DataColumn, etc) <br><br>Experience in Visual Studio 2005 and 2008, (Microsoft Office integration with Visual Studio)<br><br>Experience in SQL Server 2005, SQL Server 2008, SQL Server Reporting Services and SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS)<br><br>Experience with Web Standards, Classic Web Development Concepts (State Management, Stateless Development)<br><br>Core Ajax Fundamentals, Data Binding Fundamentals and DOM Familiarity<br><br>Charting Application Design and Development<br><br>Demonstrated proficiency in Crystal Enterprise 8.0 (Web Report Development), Source Safe, Dundas Charts <br><br>Experience in requirements evaluation (translating functional specifications into technical solutions) <br><br>Provide support / guidance to the development teams during the design, development, and testing processes<br><br>Strong analytical, organizational and hands-on problem solving skills<br><br>Sound understanding of client-server and web technologies, awareness of current Web trends and technologies<br><br>Excellent communication skills<br><br>Self-motivated with the ability to work effectively with minimal supervision while managing multiple projects<br><br>Thorough understanding of iterative software development methods<br><br>Experience with Section 508 compliance <br>df-tc</span><br><br><br><br><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblExperienceKey>Experience/Skills</span><br><span id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_lblExperience class=body>For immediate consideration, please submit your resume. Please list how many years you have experience in the required skill. Qualified candidates will be contacted for further discussion about this opportunity. <br><br>We are unable to offer sponsorship. Preference will be given to local or commutable candidates. <br><br>Thank you for your interest in Ajilon Consulting!</span><br></td></tr></table><!-- google_ad_section_end --></td></tr><tr id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_trBottom><td valign=middle align=center height=50><input type=image name=ctl00$ctl00$contentMaster$content$btnApplyJobBottom id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_content_btnApplyJobBottom title="Apply to this job" src=/App_Themes/PublicSite/Images/btn_applynow_off.jpg onclick="location.href = 'http://www.tech-centric.net/Candidate/ApplyJob.aspx?JobID=733463'; return false;" onmouseover="this.src = '/App_Themes/PublicSite/Images/btn_applynow_on.jpg'" onmouseout="this.src = '/App_Themes/PublicSite/Images/btn_applynow_off.jpg'" border=0></td></tr></table></div></td><!--end center col--><!--begin right col--><td align=right valign=top width=120><table width=120 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td valign=middle><div id=tooltop><table width=120 height=27 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td><div align=center><img id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_Tools1_imgToolsTitle title=Tools src=/App_Themes/PublicSite/Images/title_tools.jpg height=16 width=39 border=0></div></td></tr></table></div></td></tr><tr><td><div id=toolbox><table width=120 height=254 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td align=center><a id=ctl00_ctl00_contentMaster_Tools1_hhlCreateResume title="Tech Computer IT Technology Resume" href=/Candidate/Resume