</style><p class=text><p><strong>Fixed Income Application Support Specialist</strong><br><br> One of my direct financial clients located in New York, NY is looking for a Fixed Income Application Support Specialist. This client is VERY hot to hire, and will begin actively interviewing qualified candidates immediately. The client is one of the world’s largest financial services firms.  Mitchell/Martin Inc. is working directly with the Director who supervises this group, and who has the final say in hiring resources. They have budget and are ready to hire.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><b>LOCATION: New York, NY</b></p><p><b>DURATION: 6-12 Months - Right to Hire</b></p><p><b>RATE: Open</b></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>*** The Ideal Candidate at least 5 Years of experience with Fixed Income Application Support. Candidate should have excellent communication skills and can work in a fast paced environment. </p><p><b>Role specific responsibilities: <br></b>Role is for 1st / 2nd line support. </p><p>Role is approximately 10% enhancements, 70% investigations and service requests, 20% system maintenance </p><p>The successful candidate would be working in a FRONT OFFICE Application support role for at least 1.5 years in IT looking for a move to a more dynamic environment. The knowledge gained within this team is invaluable within fixed income.</p><p>Due to the nature of the markets the desks need to be supported from 7am to 7pm. This is covered on a shift basis. Weekend and Bank holiday support is often required – and is shared amongst the team.</p><p><b>Deliverables: (Criteria/results by which success can be measured)</b></p><ul><li>Quick resolution of production problems and clear feedback to traders and business management. </li><li>Ownership of problems </li><li>Maintain a good relationship with the traders, keeping them informed of resolutions to problems, show them how to make best use of the systems </li><li>Maintenance of production systems </li><li>Documentation of new procedures</li></ul></p></div><br><!-- End JObs Description --></div></div><div class="right jobdet_rcol"><div id=banners><a class=ban_upload_cv href=javascript:void(0) onclick="return LogIn('/candidate/postresume', this, -300);"><span class=left>POST YOUR RESUME</span></a></div><script type=text/javascript><!--
