	.job_desc li {margin-left:20px;}
</style><p class=text><b>Experience Apple</b><br><br>There's the typical job. Punch in, push paper, punch out, repeat. Then there's a career at Apple. Where you're encouraged to defy routine. To explore the far reaches of the possible. To travel uncharted paths. And to be a part of something far bigger than yourself. Because around here, changing the world just comes with the job description. <br><br><b>We are committed to diversity. <br><br>Apple is an Equal Opportunity Employer. <br><br>www.apple.com/jobs</b><br><br>The candidate is expected to be an experienced motivated tester with at least 4 years hands-on experience of 802.11 and/or Bluetooth testing. The job involves interoperability testing of Apple wireless products (iPhone, Portables, Desktops and Base stations) with 3rd party WLAN/BT devices to ensure a high-quality, real-world customer experience. The job involves working closely with software quality assurance and hardware engineering teams to identify issues and isolate the root cause of the problem. The candidate also needs to be a motivated, individual contributor that can work with minimal intervention or supervision as well as a team player that thrives in a fast-paced quality-conscious environment. We encourage out of box thinking that helps replicate customer use scenarios with the given resources and tools. The candidate will have the freedom to recommend new test methodology and tools provided there is sufficient justification. <br><br>Duties for this position include, but are not limited to: <br><br><li> Test and report 802.11/BT hardware and software bugs with analysis involving systems where it does and does not occur with all necessary protocol sniffer captures and traces. <br>Be a DRI (Direct Responsible Individual, aka technical lead) in a specific area of technology to make sure test tools, methodology remain current with market/competitive trends. <br>Own the quality and coverage of test plans/cases/steps in DRI area <br><li> Develop test automation scripts and maintain/expand such systems to offload mundane / routine testing <br><br><li> Four year Computer Science degree or equivalent <br><li> Four or more years of QA system test experience in IEEE 802.11 / Bluetooth technologies <br><li> In-depth knowledge of Wi-Fi 802.11N draft 2 and/or Bluetooth as well as associated protocol sniffers, test tools/methodology <br><li> Working knowledge of Mac OS X including command-line tools for debugging, analysis and automation <br><li> Exposure to at least one of the following scripting languages: AppleScript, PERL, Tcl, Bash. Candidate must demonstrate ability to write scripts. <br><li> Experience and working knowledge of network analysis and debugging tools <br><li> Ability to analyze crash logs, backtraces and assist engineers by utilizing basic debugging techniques will be a bonus</p></div><br><!-- End JObs Description --></div></div><div class="right jobdet_rcol"><div id=banners><a class=ban_upload_cv href=javascript:void(0) onclick="return LogIn('/candidate/postresume', this, -300);"><span class=left>POST YOUR RESUME</span></a></div><script type=text/javascript><!--
