	.job_desc li {margin-left:20px;}
</style><p class=text><span style="border-collapse: collapse; line-height: 14px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; "><span style="font-family: arial, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: medium; "><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: 9pt; "><strong style="font-weight: bold; ">GENERAL DESCRIPTION<br></strong>Due to continued and sustained project growth, Bluep</span><span style="font-family: arial; "><span style="font-size: 10pt; ">rint Consult</span><span style="font-size: 9pt; ">ing is hiring experienced quality assurance (QA) software testing professionals. We offer a pleasant and professional environment, reasonable expectations, and a true work/life balance for every individual. <br><br><strong style="font-weight: bold; ">PRIMARY ROLES &amp; RESPONSIBILITIES <br><ul><li><span style="font-weight: normal; ">Analyze complex requirements and use cases for the purpose of developing test plans and test scripts.</span></li><li><span style="font-weight: normal; ">Develop well-written test plans and test scripts.</span></li><li><span style="font-weight: normal; ">Execute test cases and write defect reports as appropriate into the defect-tracking tool.</span></li><li><span style="font-weight: normal; ">Execute regression test cases when development loads point releases into Test Environment.</span></li><li><span style="font-weight: normal; ">Support end users in validating the requirements of each release.</span></li><li><span style="font-weight: normal; ">Take direction for additional software testing responsibilities as required by company and/or client staff. </span></li></ul></strong></span></span><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: 9pt; "><br><strong style="font-weight: bold; ">SCHEDULES &amp; BENEFITS<br></strong>The position is stable and full-time, and the work schedule is very conducive to a well-rounded life. It is Monday through Friday, 40 hours per week, no nights, weekends, pager support or holiday coverage. We also have flexible and compressed work scheduling options that further promote a true work-life balance. Starting benefits package includes 3 weeks of vacation, 10 paid holidays, Blue Cross Blue Shield health insurance, long and short-term disability coverage, subsidized in-building gym membership, dental, vision, AFLAC, and a 401k program with company profit-sharing match. The position we are hiring for is an individual contributor role. The successful candidate will be a full-time employee of Blueprint. Our company and work site is located in downtown Phoenix. The starting salary for this position is dependent upon education and relevant software testing experience.</span></span><div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; "><span style="font-family: arial, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; "><br></span><span style="font-size: 12px; ">Professional software testing certifications, additional paid time off, and other benefits become available as employees accrue service time with the company.</span></div><div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; "><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: 9pt; "><strong style="font-weight: bold; "><br><span style="font-weight: normal; "> For prompt consideration and to learn more about Blueprint Consulting and this opportunity, apply online at www.blueprintqa.com or email your resume to info@blueprintqa.com.</span></strong></span></div></span></p></div><br><!-- End JObs Description --></div></div><div class="right jobdet_rcol"><div id=banners><a class=ban_upload_cv href=javascript:void(0) onclick="return LogIn('/candidate/postresume', this, -300);"><span class=left>POST YOUR RESUME</span></a></div><script type=text/javascript><!--
