e this job:</font><br><!-- AddThis Button BEGIN --><a class=addthis_button href="http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&username=nettemps"><img src=http://s7.addthis.com/static/btn/v2/lg-share-en.gif width=125 height=16 alt="Bookmark and Share" style=border:0></a><script type=text/javascript src="http://s7.addthis.com/js/250/addthis_widget.js#username=nettemps"></script><!-- AddThis Button END --></div><div style=clear:both></div></div><div style="margin-top:20px; margin-bottom:20px"></div><table cellpadding=4 cellspacing=0 border=0><tr><td align=center class=actionstable> &nbsp;&nbsp; <a class=links href="http://my.net-temps.com/apply.html?jobref=1274151&referer=net" target=_self onmouseover="self.status='Apply to this Job'; return true" onmouseout="self.status=''; return true"><b>Apply Online</b></a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a class=links href="http://my.net-temps.com/savejob.html?ref=capmp/post/1852.html" target=_blank onmouseover="self.status='Add this job to my Saved Jobs'; return true" onmouseout="self.status=''; return true">Save this job</a> &nbsp;&nbsp; </td></tr></table><p><table width=710 cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 border=0><tr><td align=left colspan=2><p><font class=attribute><b>Reference Number:</b></font><br><font class=text>1852</font><br><p><font class=attribute><b>Job Description:</b></font><br><font class=text>Our client is seeking an experienced middle level Systems Administrator for it's Herndon, Virginia location. This position requires US Citizenship and should have most of the following skills displayed in their resume: Redhat Linux, Oracle Application Server, Oracle 10g, Oracle11g, Apache, Tomcat, Network(ing), Windows, VMware, Perl, Shell, Backups. The salary is negotiable and we are interviewing immediately for the position. The job description is as follows:<br><br> Functional Responsibility: <br><br> &#61553; Work closely with architects in designing enterprise class solutions based on the principles of redundancy, data integrity, security and recoverability. <br> &#61553; Integrate and implement server solutions and server components such as proxy servers, web servers, application servers, database servers, directory servers, core infrastructure services (Proxy, DNS, SSH, SMTP, etc), and others<br> &#61553; Implement and troubleshoot redundant application solutions using the Oracle Application Server. <br> &#61553; Engineer solutions to meet customer requirements based on current and future server platforms.<br> &#61553; Perform maintenance activities in a large environment composed of a mix of different UNIX/Linux, Windows platforms and configurations. <br> &#61553; Trouble-shoot hardware, software and network related problems. <br> &#61553; Implement and administer archive and backup systems. <br> &#61553; Plan and maintain the network configuration of routers, switches, and firewalls associated with network traffic. Maintain existing network equipment and servers to include patches and upgrades for enhancement or security.<br> &#61553; Monitor performance and system utilization and participate in activities related to growth analysis and capacity planning.<br> &#61553; Monitor IT infrastructure, and network security.<br> &#61553; Draft, update and follow best practices and standards documentation<br> &#61553; Provide on-call support advice and technical support to various users/clients regarding operational/applications issues. Follow up with customer upon receipt of problems and provide timely status reports until problem is resolved.<br> &#61553; Stay up to date with relevant state-of-the-art technology, equipment, and/or systems. Evaluates new hardware and software technologies, and presents analysis and purchase recommendations to the administration team and to management. <br><br> Minimum/General Experience: <br><br> Five to Seven years of systems/network administration experience having strong analytical skills. Solid foundation in working with various flavors of Unix/Linux & Windows operating systems on heterogeneous hardware platforms. Working knowledge of configuration & administration of VMware Infrastructure. Experience in MAC OSX, and other operating systems is a plus.<br><br> &#61553; Strong knowledge of administering various flavors of Linux especially Red Hat Enterprise Linux Servers <br> &#61553; Experience with configuring, implementing, and troubleshooting redundant, high availability solutions using databases such as MySQL, postgres, Oracle<br> &#61553; Working knowledge of virtual environments (VMware) and storage environments (SAN, NAS)<br> &#61553; Extensive software experience with Oracle Application Server, Apache, IIS, Tomcat, sendmail, LDAP, clustering, etc.<br> &#61553; Automate tasks using scripting (Perl, Shell)<br> &#61553; Familiarity or knowledge of NIST and FISMA guidelines<br> &#61553; Performance tuning and monitoring<br> &#61553; Upgrading and patching<br> &#61553; Backups and Recovery<br> &#61553; Ability to work well with customers and in a cross-team environment <br> &#61553; Excellent interpersonal and communication skills<br> &#61553; Documentation processes and procedures<br><br><br> Education and training: BS or MS degree in Computer Science or a related discipline<br><br> US Citizenship Required<br><br><br> Go to http://www.cmp.jobs to see more jobs.</font><br><p><font class=attribute><b>Experience Level:</b></font><br><font class=text>Unspecified</font><br><p><font class=attribute><b>Requirements:</b></font><br><font class=text></font><br></td></tr><tr><td align=left valign=top width=305><p><font class=attribute><b>Location:</b></font><br><font class=text>Herndon VA</font><br><p><font class=attribute><b>Duration:</b></font><br><font class=text>Direct Placement</font><br><p><font class=attribute><b>Pay Rate:</b></font><br><font class=text>$90000/year</font><br></td><td width=405 align=right valign=center><table width=405 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td align=right class=blueborder bgcolor=E7