 releases, including automated and manual tests<br>-Building and maintaining test setups, including computers<br>-Ability to recreate and validate 3rd level support issues.<br><br><br>Requirements:<br><br>-Minimum 3+ years related experience in software system test, problem resolution, and regression testing<br>-Strong understanding of software engineering and testing principles<br>-Experience writing SQL queries.&nbsp; Knowledge using Sybase a plus<br>-Experience testing and troubleshooting real-time database applications and developing and maintaining user documentation helpful<br>-Ability to document defects and follow-up on resolution<br>-Working Knowledge of Operating Systems � Windows, Linux <br>-Ability to write Batch Files (Windows) and/or Shell scripts (Linux) and Perl Scripts<br>-Strong analytical skills, excellent verbal and written communication skills and be able to work successfully with others in a team environment<br>-Ability to achieve quality results on tight timelines working long hours<br>-Self starter and able to work independently when necessary<br>-Experience with or understanding of communication protocols a plus<br>-Experience with or understanding of software hardware drivers a plus<br>-Ability&nbsp; to&nbsp; deploy the software to be tested onto the test environment<br>-BS/MS in Computer Science/Engineering or related discipline<br>-Interpersonal skills required to influence team members, listen to customer requirements, and an openness to moving into other roles as time and business requirements dictate<p><table><tr><td><b>Category:</b></td><td>Information Technology</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td></tr><tr><td><b>Location:</b></td><td>Stratford, CT</td></tr><tr><td><b>County:</b></td><td>Fairfield County</td></tr><tr><td><b>ZIP Code:</b></td><td>06497</td></tr><tr><td><b>Pay Rate:</b></td><td>Open</td></tr><tr><td><b>Job Terms:</b></td><td>full time</td></tr><tr><td valign=top><b>Company:</b></td><td><a target=_blank href="/public/vrc.mpl