mg src=/images/tweet_share.png width=31 height=27 alt="Bookmark and Share" style=border:0></a><script type=text/javascript src=http://s7.addthis.com/js/200/addthis_widget.js></script>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a onclick="window.open('/public/flag_content.mpl?cid=6376910','flag_content_window','menubar=no,width=500,height=400,toolbar=no,status=no,location=no');" onmouseover="window.status='Flag Content.'; return true;" onmouseout="window.status=''; return true;"><img src=/images/job_flag_content.gif border=0 title="Flag Content"></a><hr></td></tr></table><p><form action=/public/auto_apply_area.mpl method=POST><input type=hidden value=6376910 name=id><table width=410 border=0><tr><td valign=top align=right><input type=submit value="Apply to Job"></td></tr></table></form><h3>Sr Quality Analyst</h3><i>Posted:&nbsp; December 6, 2010</i><br><p style="word-wrap:break-word; width:390">Our client, a LEADER in the Capital Markets industry has the following consulting opportunity available through RMS Computer Corporation working onsite at our client on the following project. <br><br>NO AGENCIES PLEASE<br><br>LOCAL CANDIDATES ONLY&nbsp; <br><br>Job Description: The IT Quality Sr. Analyst role is an individual contributor and member of the IT group in Investment Bank.� <br>Investment Bank is a third party hedge fund administrator offering services, and accompanying applications, for trades processing, portfolio accounting, transfer agency, tax and other services.� Applications include both internally developed external vendor products.� The IT Quality Sr. Analyst is responsible to lead Quality Assurance project deliverables and planning for Investment Bank. <br>This includes oversight of test planning, strategies and testing metrics. <br>Specific job description includes:<br> - Assesses and estimates efforts on moderate to high complex projects and tracks progress.<br> - Test quality control on a wide range of projects and analyzes to ensure that software meets or exceeds specified standards and end-user requirements. This may include the highest level of problems where analysis of situations or data requires an in-depth evaluation of various factors.<br> - Creates test plans and scripts with consideration to end-to-end system flows.<br> - Analyzes test results procedures for future replication and creates test data to thoroughly test positive and negative program logic.<br> - Identifies, recommends and implements process improvements to enhance testing strategies.<br> - Analyzes requirements and design aspects of projects. Interfaces with project leads and other development organizations.� <br> - Develops organizational process improvements, local process improvement and technology initiatives<br> - Create metrics for cost, effort, and milestones of Quality activities on department level.<br> - Assesses trends and determines root cause of problems and recommends solutions towards continuous improvements and streamlining of processes.<br>This role requires senior level of experience in an IT project leadership role. Should exhibit strong execution capabilities and independent work experience.Job <br><br>Skills/Qualifications: Preferably, the candidate also has a strong operational or technology background. <br>Soft skills include excellent oral and written communications as well as proven organizational skills. <br>Candidate must be familiar with working in a matrix environment, across geographic time zones. <br>Proven analytical and problem solving skills<p>Please refer to job code <b>10-01712</b> when responding to this ad.<p><table><tr><td><b>Category:</b></td><td>Information Technology</td></tr><tr><td></td><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;>&nbsp;<a target=_blank href="/public/csearch.mpl?search_string=TEC776%20or%20Other%20Information%20Technology%20or%20Information%20Techno