ages/tweet_share.png width=31 height=27 alt="Bookmark and Share" style=border:0></a><script type=text/javascript src=http://s7.addthis.com/js/200/addthis_widget.js></script>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a onclick="window.open('/public/flag_content.mpl?cid=7327701','flag_content_window','menubar=no,width=500,height=400,toolbar=no,status=no,location=no');" onmouseover="window.status='Flag Content.'; return true;" onmouseout="window.status=''; return true;"><img src=/images/job_flag_content.gif border=0 title="Flag Content"></a><hr></td></tr></table><p><form action=/public/require_login.mpl method=POST><input type=hidden value=7327701 name=id><input type=hidden value=9272 name=m><input type=hidden value=10%2D06563 name=c><input type=hidden value=jc name=partner><table width=410 border=0><tr><td valign=top align=right><input type=submit value="Apply to Job"></td></tr></table></form><h3>Firewall Engineer</h3><i>Posted:&nbsp; December 6, 2010</i><br><p style="word-wrap:break-word; width:390">&nbsp; <br>Firewall Engineer Staff Consultant <br><br>Posting Description&nbsp; <br><br>Support the maintenance and administration of our client firewalls. Provide support to all CIRT functions and using C3 staff and provide onsite supplemental staff required to operate the Forensic office. Responsible for reporting all incidents and ensuring the management approves these reports and that the reports are within timelines mandated by the US-CERT reporting instruction.<br>Perform vulnerability and security scans of existing production network components, paths, networks, sub-networks, systems and software as required. Verification of all tests shall be recorded in an operations log and archived electronically.<br><br>Additional duties include:<br>- Collect and analyze data obtained by the clients security tools.<br>- Test and install patches and fixes for security vulnerabilities in vendor software.<br>- Participate in reviews and analysis of projects that have an impact on the IT security of the client.<br>- Analyze security and firewall logs and investigate all irregularities as needed.<br>- Provide Investigation, coordination, reporting and follow-up of IT Security incidents.<br>- Periodically run password-cracking tools to ensure user and system passwords meet the minimum strength requirements established in clients Security Policy.<br>- Be actively monitoring security newsgroups, announcements and mailing lists and report to the Division Chief with recommendations for patching, mitigating or accept risk.<br>- Must keep up with the latest Security Issues, Trends, and developments by researching and attending briefings, classes and conferences.<br>- Alerts the SOC to all intrusion attempts and report findings to appropriate parties. Responsible for maintaining copies of all reported Firewall incidents, and be able to report quickly on all reporting requirements, scheduled and ad hoc, as required by Federal and agency programs.<br>- Investigates available and advanced technologies of automation and information systems processes, and then applies basic management principles to adapt to a variety of subject matter situations to increase the scope and effectiveness of the Firewalls.<br>- Provide technical resolutions for problems with existing software and systems management.<br>- Must maintain in good standing CISSP.<br>- Performs other IT Security duties as assigned.<br><br>Previous large enterprise wide security monitoring and management experience and a secret clearance. Must be a self starter able to provide expert security monitoring, management and forensics with little or no direct supervision.<br>Candidate should be experienced with Checkpoint, Juniper, various IDS, SIEM tools and LogLogic and should be able to configure Checkpoint and Juniper firewalls and to operate and tune ISS and Juniper IDS/IDP solutions. Candidates should know how to use Smart Dashboard and Netscreen Security Manager (NSM)).<br><br>Education/Training/Certifications Required/Desired:<br>Bachelors degree in Network Security preferred but is not a must for a person with sufficient network security experience.<br><br>Unique skills/Additional Requirements: (Clearances, etc.)<br>Environment may require Secret clearance in future so candidate should be clearable.<br><br>Normal Work Hours:<br>Mon - Thu or Tue - Fri, 7am - 5pm plus other hours as needed 24/7<br>Initial schedule:&nbsp; person should plan on either 10pm&nbsp; 8am three days a week and a fourth day that runs 12noon to 10pm OR 3am&nbsp; 1pm four days a week. <p><p>Please refer to job code <b>10-06563</b> when responding to this ad.<p><table><tr><td><b>Location:</b></td><td>Alexandria, VA</td></tr><tr><td><b>County:</b></td><td>Alexandria City County</td></tr><tr><td><b>ZIP Code:</b></td><td>22301</td></tr><tr><td><b>Pay Rate:</b></td><td>Open</td></tr><tr><td><b>Job Terms:</b></td><td>contract-to-hire</td></tr><tr><td valign=top><b>Company:</b></td><td><a target=_blank href="/public/vrc.mpl?id=7552&utm_source=JobCircle&utm_medium=web&utm_campaign=classified_detail&utm_content=company_profile">Kaztronix, LLC</a></td></tr><tr><td><b>Phone:</b></td><td>email only</td></tr><tr><td><b>Fax:</b></td><td>email only</td></tr></table><form action=/public/require_login.mpl method=POST><input type=hidden value=7327701 name=id><input type=hidden value=9272 name=m><input type=hidden value=10%2D06563 name=c><input type=hidden value=jc name=partner><table width=410 border=0><tr><td valign=top align=right><input type=submit value="Apply to Job"></td></tr></table></form><!-- [ END CLASSIFIED DATA ] --></td></tr></table></td><td bgcolor=#ffffff><img src=/images/spacer.gif width=3></td></tr></table><!-- END CONTENTBOX --><!-- END CONTENT AREA --></td><!-- END CENTER COLUMN --><!-- BEGIN RIGHT COLUMN --><td width=170 valign=top height=100%