					</script><div class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style" style="float:right; margin-top:5px;"><a class=addthis_button_facebook></a><a class=addthis_button_delicious></a><a class=addthis_button_email></a><a class=addthis_button_favorites></a><span class=addthis_separator>|</span><a href="http://addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&pub=vaweb2007" class=addthis_button_expanded>More</a></div><script type=text/javascript src="http://s7.addthis.com/js/250/addthis_widget.js#pub=vaweb2007"></script></div></div><h4 class=jobView_company><em>Company:</em> Northrop Grumman&nbsp;<br><span class=listLocation><em style=font-size:11px;>Location:</em> Atlanta, Georgia </span></h4><ul id=jobSummary><li><em>Salary:</em> Not Specified </li><li><em>Category:</em> Information Tech / Computer</li><li><em>Date Posted:</em> 12/07/2010</li><li><em>Travel Required:</em> Not Specified</li><li><em>Security Clearance:</em> No</li><li><em>Work Type:</em> Any</li></ul><h4 class=insideTitle title="Job Description">Job Description</h4><blockquote class=insideBlock><p> Job Title: Software Development Analyst 3 <br>Profession: Computer Engineering and Information Technology - &gt; Software Design/Development <br><br>Title: Software Development Analyst 3Category: Information SystemsLocation: Atlanta, GA / USA | Sector: Information SystemsDescription:Northrop Grumman Information Systems sector is seeking a Software Development Analyst to join our team of qualified, diverse individuals in defining the future. This position and will be located in Atlanta, GA. Where Technology and Teamwork come together.. . The qualified candidate will provide assistance in the research, design and development of a set of solutions for delivering health communication via the web, particularly using open source technologies such as JAVA, PHP and Python. The candidate will be expected to be able to handle development from server applications to carry through to front end development. While the candidate will often be working with User Experience staff to develop requirements, the developer should be able to review a project proposal and develop initial requirements independently as well. Roles and Responsibilities:Responsible for developing new products to meet business needs. Research new platforms such as social networking platforms such as Facebook Apps and OpenSocial Standards as well as new trends in web such as Semantic Web and Real-Time Web opportunities. Development of tools that partner websites and consumers can use to display CDC content. This will be accomplished through the use of various tools and standards such as web services for APIs, open source tools, as well as proprietary tools needed to develop against various platforms. Research applicable and emerging tools, APIs, Web Services, open source trends and development methodologies and adapt those accordingly. Serve as a lead for research into open source platforms and solutions. Minimum Qualifications:To be considered for this position, you must minimally meet the knowledge, skills, and abilities listed below:Open Source Development:5+ years of experience developing applications using Java, XML, OOP and Web Services5+ years of experience developing applications using other open source languages and technologies such as PHP, Python, XML, XMLST, XHTML, CSS, JavaScript, AJAX5+ years of experience developing multi layered/tiered web applications using sever based web technologies for multiple browsers5+ years experience with MS SQL Server 2000/2005 including T-SQL, Stored Procedures, User Defined Functions, Views, Triggers, Roles, and DTS/SSIS packages5+ years experience with MySQL5+ years experience with XML, XSLT, XQuery, XPathDevelop and unit test web solutionsPerform architecture, product enhancement and maintenance development tasks. Excellent understanding of best practices and design patterns in Object Oriented Programming. Perform code reviews and manage project commitments. Provide development estimates and identify risks associated with the effort. Experience with UML, Visual SourceSafe, IIS 6. 0+, Windows 2000/2003 Server; Understanding of Windows Security, Active Directory. Keeps up to date with Open Source technologiesFollow development methodology, policies, procedures and standards. Other Development Experience:Demonstrated ability to research new languages, concepts and platforms such as OpenSocial, Semantic Web, Flex, and . NET using computer science methodologies and OOP. Interactive Development (i. e. AJAX/DOM/HTML/CSS):3+ years experience with XHTML, CSS3+ years experience with AJAX, JavaScriptSolid experience working with web-browser DOM using JavaScript, AJAX and CSSExperience with cross browser/platform developmentExperience with jQuery and JSON is a plusPreferred Qualifications:Candidates with these desired skills will be given preferential consideration:Excellent understanding of best practices in programming and computer science researchAbility to take creative and technical direction and develop concepts based on those. Background in quality control and usabilityCollaborate with the business owners to understand business requirements. Provide prototype</p></blockquote><div id=applyLink align=center><a href="/my.job/search/page=applyjob/" title="Apply to Job" onclick rel=nofollow>Click here to apply now</a></div></div></div><div style=clear:both;><h3 class=freeModule_hdr>More jobs you may like:</h3><div class=resultsSubset><table width=100% class=resultsList border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 summary="Job.com View of JobSearch Records" style="clear: both;"><col width=60%><col width=40%><tr><td valign=top colspan=2 style=border-bottom:0;padding-top:8px;><div style=float:right;margin:3px;><h2 class=postDate_results title="Job Posted on 12/01">Post date: <em>12/01</em></h2></div><h2 class=jobTitle_results><a id=link66890216 href="/my.job/search/page=jobview/key=66890216/" class=bold title="View the full ad for LAN/WAN Engineer Internship - $48,000 - $72,