						addthis_brand = "Job.com";
						addthis_pub    = "vaweb2007";     
					</script><div class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style" style="float:right; margin-top:5px;"><a class=addthis_button_facebook></a><a class=addthis_button_delicious></a><a class=addthis_button_email></a><a class=addthis_button_favorites></a><span class=addthis_separator>|</span><a href="http://addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&pub=vaweb2007" class=addthis_button_expanded>More</a></div><script type=text/javascript src="http://s7.addthis.com/js/250/addthis_widget.js#pub=vaweb2007"></script></div></div><h4 class=jobView_company><em>Company:</em> CaridianBCT&nbsp;<br><span class=listLocation><em style=font-size:11px;>Location:</em> Lakewood, Colorado </span></h4><ul id=jobSummary><li><em>Salary:</em> Not Specified </li><li><em>Category:</em> Information Tech / Computer</li><li><em>Date Posted:</em> 12/07/2010</li><li><em>Travel Required:</em> Not Specified</li><li><em>Security Clearance:</em> No</li><li><em>Work Type:</em> Any</li></ul><h4 class=insideTitle title="Job Description">Job Description</h4><blockquote class=insideBlock><p> Job Title: SAP ABAP Programmer Analyst <br>Profession: Computer Engineering and Information Technology - &gt; Software Design/Development <br><br>SAP ABAP Programmer Analyst Job ID: MM-0419 Description:ORGANIZATIONAL OVERVIEW:CaridianBCT is a global leader in the blood bank and transfusion medicine industry, investing in research and development focused on enhancing blood quality, safety and supply. It provides technology, products and services to blood centers, hospitals, and scientific, clinical and biotech researchers. Job Summary:Position provides analysis and technical expertise in an existing and emerging SAP environment. Performs a broad range of tasks which include research, analysis, design, configuration, testing, maintenance, support, training, and implementation of information technology solutions in the SAP ABAP environment. Essential Duties and Responsibilities: * Within the context of the ITS/Business Strategic Plan, operates independently in various activities such as research, selection, and implementation of technology solutions. * Applies highly professional business and/or technical knowledge when working with clients, other ITS groups, and vendors in activities such as identifying options, selection, analyzing, designing, installation, coding, maintenance, and testing of information technology solutions. * Responsible for providing technical assistance, problem resolution, support, and training for clients and other ITS groups. * Shares responsibility with team members for 24-hour on-call problem resolution. * Responsible for recommending, implementing, creating, maintaining, interpreting, improving, summarizing, and reporting on the performance indicators for the technology area. * Responsible for establishing, interpreting, and executing departmental procedures for the technology area. Minimum Qualification Requirements: * Knowledge required to perform at this level is generally acquired through completion of a Bachelor's degree in the area of Computer Science Engineering or Business; and generally a minimum of 5 years experience in a related field. * Requires in-depth knowledge of SAP ABAP having a minimum of 5 years experience as a Programmer/Analyst with experience directly in developing ABAP programs, ABAP customizations, and iDoc work. * Demonstrated ability to conduct research and recommend changes in an existing, changing, or emerging environment. * Demonstrated ability to analyze business/technical problems and select, design, or implement information technology solutions in accordance with business needs. * Demonstrated effective oral and written communication skills with the ability to communicate technical information to non-technical personnel. Demonstrated working knowledge of multiple business disciplines. * Demonstrated ability to accept personal accountability and ownership for areas of responsibility. Pursue solutions and make decisions. * Demonstrated ability to initiate, promote, and exhibit team-oriented behavior. * Demonstrated initiative to continue life-long learning. * Dedicated to quality client service and proactive and responsive to client needs. * Takes initiative to understand customers and their environment. * Requires flexibility to adapt to and willingness to learn new technologies. * Requires strong orientation to customer satisfaction. * Requires ability and willingness to work on multiple projects at one time and be able to adapt to changing priorities. * Requires ability to work with team members to deliver on time and on budget committed results to customers. * Requires ability and willingness to educate and train others. <br><br>Desired Attributes <br><br>Profession: Computer Engineering and Information Technology - &gt; Software Design/Development <br>Application Types: Operating systems/Device drivers <br>Application Types: Application development tools <br>Application Types: Application integration/Middleware <br>Application Types: Data management applications <br>Operating Systems: UNIX/Linux <br>Programming Languages: SQL <br>Programming Languages: ABAP (SAP) <br>Level of Experience: Individual contributor <br>Industry: IT/</p></blockquote><div id=applyLink align=center><a href="/my.job/search/page=applyjob/" title="Apply to Job" onclick rel=nofollow>Click here to apply now</a></div></div></div><div style=clear:both;><h3 class=freeModule_hdr>More jobs you may like:</h3><div class=resultsSubset><table width=100% class=resultsList border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 summary="Job.com View of JobSearch Records" style="clear: both;"><col width=60%><col width=40%><tr><td valign=top colspan=2 style=border-bottom:0;padding-top:8px;><div style=float:right;margin:3px;><h2 class=postDate_results title="Job Posted on 12/06">Post date: <em>12/06</em></h2></div><h2 class=jobTitle_results><a id=link66890226 href="/my.job/search/page=jobview/key=66890226/" class=bold title="View the full ad for LAN/WAN Engi