					</script><div class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style" style="float:right; margin-top:5px;"><a class=addthis_button_facebook></a><a class=addthis_button_delicious></a><a class=addthis_button_email></a><a class=addthis_button_favorites></a><span class=addthis_separator>|</span><a href="http://addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&pub=vaweb2007" class=addthis_button_expanded>More</a></div><script type=text/javascript src="http://s7.addthis.com/js/250/addthis_widget.js#pub=vaweb2007"></script></div></div><h4 class=jobView_company><em>Company:</em> Fuhu, Inc.&nbsp;<br><span class=listLocation><em style=font-size:11px;>Location:</em> El Segundo, California </span></h4><ul id=jobSummary><li><em>Salary:</em> Not Specified </li><li><em>Category:</em> Information Tech / Computer</li><li><em>Date Posted:</em> 12/07/2010</li><li><em>Travel Required:</em> Not Specified</li><li><em>Security Clearance:</em> No</li><li><em>Work Type:</em> Any</li></ul><h4 class=insideTitle title="Job Description">Job Description</h4><blockquote class=insideBlock><p> Job Title: Interaction Designer / Information Architect <br>Profession: Computer Engineering and Information Technology - &gt; User Interface Design <br><br>Interaction Designer / Information ArchitectKey Duties and Responsibilities * Develop user interaction model, site maps, work-flows, prototypes, and interface guidelines * Conduct usability research and translate the findings into design improvements * Create iterative interface designs and design specs * Collaborate closely with engineering and design teams to implement and ensure the development of a consistent and effective user experience * Lead interaction design through the entire product lifecycle, providing a range of tools and deliverables, including: o - use cases, user task flows o - user interface concepts and interaction models o - storyboards o - annotated wireframes o - information architecture, navigational structure o - documentation of design concept in detailed UI specs * Identify appropriate user research techniques and metrics for gauging success. * Guide product direction and set UI requirements based on user research, functional requirements, and business goals. * Conduct user and design research including: usability studies, user surveys, prototype testing, competitive product analysis, and latest industry & design trend research. * Present and communicate conceptual ideas and design rationale to the team * Document actions by creating functional descriptions and completing functional specifications with product manager. Requirements * Bachelors degree, or greater in Computer Science, Graphic Design or related field; strong technical background a plus * Minimum of 5+ years of experience on a user experience team with a track record of defining interaction design on large-scale web, mobile and/or desktop applications. * At least 5 years experience in a software development environment. * Excellent conceptual, problem-solving and communication skills * Experience building wire-frames, low and high fidelity prototypes, storyboards, and information architecture mapping * Innate passion for improving the online world and a desire to continually increase customer satisfaction * Solid portfolio of previous projects or work and work/content; references will be checked against examples. * Solid working knowledge of CSS, HTML, Javascript, AJAX, and design skills in Photoshop, Dreamweaver, Expression or other design package. * Strong knowledge of cross-platform compatibility required. * Understanding of issues of accessibility in UI design. * Excellent verbal and written communication. * Must be self-motivated to prioritize and manage work load and meet critical project milestones and deadlines. * Must be an effective problem solver. * Excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to build good working relationships. * Entrepreneurial, self-starter with hands-on approach * A hunger to learn and ability to flourish in a dynamic, high-growth environment <br><br>Desired Attributes <br><br>Profession: Computer Engineering and Information Technology - &gt; User Interface Design <br>Web Design Activities: Site map development <br>Web Design Activities: CSS/Stylesheet development <br>System Type (Type of Product): Telecommunication/Mobile phone software <br>System Architecture: Client/Server systems <br>Web Development Tools: AJAX <br>Web Development Tools: HTML <br>Web Development Tools: Javascript <br>Design Tools: DreamWeaver <br>Design Tools: Photoshop</p></blockquote><div id=applyLink align=center><a href="/my.job/search/page=applyjob/" title="Apply to Job" onclick rel=nofollow>Click here to apply now</a></div></div></div><div style=clear:both;><h3 class=freeModule_hdr>More jobs you may like:</h3><div class=resultsSubset><table width=100% class=resultsList border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 summary="Job.com View of JobSearch Records" style="clear: both;"><col width=60%><col width=40%><tr><td valign=top colspan=2 style=border-bottom:0;padding-top:8px;><div style=float:right;margin:3px;><h2 class=postDate_results title="Job Posted on 12/07">Post date: <em>12/07</em></h2></div><h2 class=jobTitle_results><a id=link61483788 href="/my.job/search/page=jobview/key=61483788/" class=bold title="View the full ad for Query Optimizer Architect">Query Optimizer Architect</a></h2><h4>Teradata</h4></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc;padding-bottom:8px;">El Segundo, California</td><td align=right style="padding-right:3px;white-space:nowrap;padding-right:10px;border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc;padding-bottom:8px;" width=40%><a id=link61483788 href="/my.job/search/page=jobview/key=61483788/" class=bold title="View the full ad for Query Optimizer Architect">View Job &raquo;</a></td></tr><tr><td valign=top colspan=2 style=border-bottom:0;padding-top:8px;><div style=float:right;margin:3px;><h2 class=postDate_results title="Job Posted on 12/07">Post date: <em>12/07</em></h2></div><h2 class=jobTi