					</script><div class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style" style="float:right; margin-top:5px;"><a class=addthis_button_facebook></a><a class=addthis_button_delicious></a><a class=addthis_button_email></a><a class=addthis_button_favorites></a><span class=addthis_separator>|</span><a href="http://addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&pub=vaweb2007" class=addthis_button_expanded>More</a></div><script type=text/javascript src="http://s7.addthis.com/js/250/addthis_widget.js#pub=vaweb2007"></script></div></div><h4 class=jobView_company><em>Company:</em> Atmospheric and Environmental Research, Inc.&nbsp;<br><span class=listLocation><em style=font-size:11px;>Location:</em> Lexington, Massachusetts </span></h4><ul id=jobSummary><li><em>Salary:</em> Not Specified </li><li><em>Category:</em> Information Tech / Computer</li><li><em>Date Posted:</em> 12/07/2010</li><li><em>Travel Required:</em> Not Specified</li><li><em>Security Clearance:</em> No</li><li><em>Work Type:</em> Any</li></ul><h4 class=insideTitle title="Job Description">Job Description</h4><blockquote class=insideBlock><p> Job Title: Software Engineer <br>Profession: Computer Engineering and Information Technology - &gt; Software Design/Development <br><br>Software EngineerJob Code: 2-SWE-20100224 Location: US-MA-LexingtonExperience (Years): 2 Category: Engineering - All Openings More information about this job:Overview:Atmospheric and Environmental Research, Inc. , established in 1977 and headquartered in Lexington, Massachusetts is a wholly-owned subsidiary of ISO, Inc. of Jersey City, NJ. AER is an award winning environmental research and consulting company with demonstrated expertise in remote sensing, radiative transfer modeling, climate modeling, ensemble weather prediction, oceanography, space weather, atmospheric modeling, planetary sciences, and a provider of medium and long range forecasts for the Energy and Financial Markets. Responsibilities:Atmospheric and Environmental Research (AER) has several openings available to develop cutting edge software tools and analysis for our Space Weather Division. Applicants are sought to assist in the development of both theoretical and empirical data assimilation models. Specific areas of interest are solar, magnetosphere, ionosphere, and the coupling of large scale models, but all candidates with the necessary skills and career interests are encouraged to apply. The work involves participation in programs that include model development, real-time data assimilation, validation, and development. Successful applicants will have opportunities to contribute to scientific presentations and publications as well as R&D proposals and reports. Qualifications:MS or BS (with 2-5 years experience) in physical sciences, engineering, physics or related field. Solid computer experience with skill in web technologies, relational database, scientific visualization, and scientific algorithm development. Strong technical and communication skills, teamwork, problem solving and customer interaction skills in a fast-paced R&D environment. Ability to obtain security clearance and US citizenship required. AER offers a competitive salary and benefits package and is an EEO/AA employer. <br><br>Desired Attributes <br><br>Profession: Computer Engineering and Information Technology - &gt; Software Design/Development <br>Application Types: Data management applications <br>Application Types: Enterprise business applications <br>Level of Experience: Individual contributor <br>Industry: Consulting/Professional Services</p></blockquote><div id=applyLink align=center><a href="/my.job/search/page=applyjob/" title="Apply to Job" onclick rel=nofollow>Click here to apply now</a></div></div></div><div style=clear:both;><h3 class=freeModule_hdr>More jobs you may like:</h3><div class=resultsSubset><table width=100% class=resultsList border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 summary="Job.com View of JobSearch Records" style="clear: both;"><col width=60%><col width=40%><tr><td