						addthis_brand = "Job.com";
						addthis_pub    = "vaweb2007";     
					</script><div class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style" style="float:right; margin-top:5px;"><a class=addthis_button_facebook></a><a class=addthis_button_delicious></a><a class=addthis_button_email></a><a class=addthis_button_favorites></a><span class=addthis_separator>|</span><a href="http://addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&pub=vaweb2007" class=addthis_button_expanded>More</a></div><script type=text/javascript src="http://s7.addthis.com/js/250/addthis_widget.js#pub=vaweb2007"></script></div></div><h4 class=jobView_company><em>Company:</em> Motorola&nbsp;<br><span class=listLocation><em style=font-size:11px;>Location:</em> Sunnyvale, California </span></h4><ul id=jobSummary><li><em>Salary:</em> Not Specified </li><li><em>Category:</em> Information Tech / Computer</li><li><em>Date Posted:</em> 12/07/2010</li><li><em>Travel Required:</em> Not Specified</li><li><em>Security Clearance:</em> No</li><li><em>Work Type:</em> Any</li></ul><h4 class=insideTitle title="Job Description">Job Description</h4><blockquote class=insideBlock><p> Job Title: CXD Principal Staff Design Research Engineer Job <br>Profession: Computer Engineering and Information Technology - &gt; User Interface Design <br><br>CXD Principal Staff Design Research Engineer <br><br>Job ID 95070 <br>Location <br>UNITED STATES - CA - SUNNYVALE <br><br>Job Category Research Engineering , Other Engineering <br>Position Type <br>Experienced <br><br>Relocation Provided <br>Domestic/In-Country <br><br>Education Required <br>Masters <br><br>Experience Required <br>5 - 10 <br><br>Basic Qualifications <br>* Masters degree <br>* Minimum 5+ years of engineering experience in Human Factors <br><br>Department Description Gettin our Moto back! <br><br>Come join the Worlds Largest Startup as Motorolas Mobile Devices business launches a new future for mobile products and services in 2010. <br><br>The Consumer Experience Design team (CXD) is searching for passionate designers to help pull the company towards our inevitable future of highly connected, social experiences. Our ambition to make Motorola a recognized leader in digital design is bolstered by our technologies which provide us with a palette for creating richer, more cinematic experiences that are adaptable to a world of diverse users. <br><br>Youll be joining one of the largest design organizations in the world, with offices in the US, China, Korea and Brazil. We believe in ourselves, our future and our heritage in Motorola. We believe we can do anything. We believe in the power of networks. We believe we can make a difference. <br><br>In everything we do, we employ an iterative, user-centered design approach in order to optimize business strategies, build our brand develop rich experiences and ensure usability. Specifically, the Interaction Design Team collaborates closely with global telecom service providers and internal work partners to create compelling, usable and innovative mobile experiences for over 100 million worldwide users. We create seamless solutions that include multimedia, calling, connectivity, messaging and productivity applications. <br><br>Scope of Responsibilities/Expectations <br>The Principal Staff Human Factors Engineer will apply skills in advanced, generative research methods to the design of physical and digital mobile device user interfaces. You will participate in collaborative projects as a member of a high-energy international team committed to developing innovative, usable, emotionally engaging products. <br><br>Works as part of a multidisciplinary team to design a product and/or works as part of a multidisciplinary team to further our basic research and understandings of users. <br>Performs human factors research: Defines studies Creates methods, refines methods; Conducts studies; analyzes data; writes reports with recommendations. Works with CXD, marketing and engineering teams on product definition and design and support multiple products. <br><br>Duties and Responsibilities: <br>Is able to identify potential usability issues. <br>Understands and acts on relevant usability issues. Decides on what to test and at what level to test, e. g. heuristic, informal or formal. <br><br>Works within Human Factors and Audio teams <br>Works within CXD <br>Works with marketing and engineering teams <br>Works on products as subject matter expert <br><br>Designs research inventing new methods <br>Uses either existing research or creates research to answer novel questions. <br><br>Specific Knowledge/Skills <br> A passion to develop great products <br> Minimum of 5 years experience designing, executing, and reporting advanced design research <br> Proven effectiveness in driving research results into tangible outcomes in products <br> Experience researching and designing both physical and digital product interaction <br> Ability to work as part of a cross-functional team with limited supervision <br> Strong ability to articulate and drive common understanding with cross-functional work partners and senior management <br> Experience in the development of UI simulations and/or automated data collection tools as required for research (strongly desired) <br> A graduate degree in Human Factors: interaction design, psychology, design research, etc. <br> Willingness to travel internationally <br><br>Desired Attributes <br><br>Profession: Computer Engineering and Information Techno</p></blockquote><div id=applyLink align=center><a href="/my.job/search/page=applyjob/" title="Apply to Job" onclick rel=nofollow>Click here to apply now</a></div></div></div><div style=clear:both;><h3 class=freeModule_hdr>More jobs you may like:</h3><div class=resultsSubset><table width=100% class=resultsList border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 summary="Job.com View of JobSearch Records" style="clear: both;"><col width=60%><col width=40%><tr><td valign=top colspan=2 style=border-bottom:0;padding-top:8px;><div style=float:right;margin:3px;><h2 class=postDate_results title="Job Posted on 12/01">Pos