/share_job_1.gif></a></h5><a href=javascript:// id=emailJob onclick=mailToFriend()><img src=http://l.yimg.com/a/i/us/hj/gr/email-job3.gif></a><a href="/jobseeker/jobsearch/job_save_and_confirm.html?job_id=JL80YQBBIJ8&crumb=&search_url="><img src=http://l.yimg.com/a/i/us/hj/gr/save-job3.gif></a><a href onclick="print(); return false;"><img src=http://l.yimg.com/a/i/us/hj/gr/print3.gif></a><span id=repabContainer_1 style="border: 0px none ; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;"><a id=repabManage_1 style=_cursor:hand;cursor:pointer;><img id=report_abuse_img_1 src=http://l.yimg.com/a/i/us/hj/gr/report_abuse.gif></a></span></div><br clear=all></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div id=jobDescription><strong>About Equinix<br><br></strong>Equinix, Inc. (Nasdaq: EQIX) operates International Business Exchange (IBX) data centers offering businesses a place to reliably run their operations and securely exchange critical information in North America, Europe and Asia-Pacific. Every day, without compromise, the people who control the world&#39;s most valued information assets place their trust in us, leveraging our insight, expertise and world-class service to protect and connect what matters to them most--their information. <br><br><strong>Why Equinix</strong><br><br>As a recognized global leader in its industry, Equinix employs dedicated, driven experts who take pride in their work. When you choose to work for Equinix, you&#39;re not just picking a job, you&#39;re embarking on a career. You&#39;re not just working at a company, you&#39;re joining a vital, global team.<br><br>End User Support Technicians are responsible for the response and diagnosis of end-user support tickets. These support tickets are intermediate to complex in nature, include problem recognition, research, resolution and follow-up. Works with end users to help them better understand Equinix technology. Reports to the End User Technology Manager. Escalates more complex problems to senior support personnel or management to expedite resolution. Interacts with management to plan and complete projects to ensure corporate goals are being met. Requires a high degree of professionalism and timeliness, while meeting or exceeding customer expectations and service level commitments.<br><br><strong>Responsibilities</strong><br><ul><li>Troubleshoot and resolve Windows and Mac desktops/laptops hardware and software issues via Altiris HelpDesk</li><li>Configure, upgrade, and relocate PC hardware and peripherals</li><li>Windows 2008 AD account administration</li><li>Help build a rich IT knowledge base</li><li>Solid understanding of system administration, networking concepts and technologies.</li><li>Administer and maintain Blackberry and iPhone handhelds </li><li>Completes desktop related projects as assigned (e.g., office moves, printer installation, etc).</li><li>Provide top notch customer service</li><li>Ability to lift 50 lbs</li><li>Other duties as assigned</li></ul><br><br><strong>Qualifications & Experience</strong><br><ul><li>Knowledge of TCP/IP</li><li>Advanced knowledge with Windows XP and Office 2003</li><li>2 - 4 years experience working in an IT Helpdesk environment</li><li>Bachelor degree, an industry certification or equivalent work experience</li><li>Detail oriented and deadline driven</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</li><li>Strong customer service background</li></ul><br><br>**Equinix is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer.<br><a target=_new href="/jobseeker/jobsearch/linkoff_newwin.html?jid=JL80YQBBIJ8&lo=http%3A%2F%2Fequinix.contacthr.com%2F17895292&sign=/SIG=11591nihk&host=equinix.contacthr.com&source="><h3>APPLY TO THIS JOB HERE</a></h3><br><br><br><img height=1 width=1 border=0 src=http://equinix.contacthr.com/17895292.jpg><br><br></div><div id=shadow-container style=margin-top:3px;><div class=shadow1><div class=shadow2><div class=shadow3><div class=container><div id=applyButtonBarBottom style=height:76px;padding:0px;background