	  --><div id=description_col><dl class=buttons><dd class=save><a id=saveJob href=# title="Save Job">Save this job</a></dd><dd class=email><a href="/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=305&dockey=xml/c/9/c99c43e659e24135469fc9075265adc4&source=null&ral=JobSearch?



					op=302







					%26dockey=xml/c/9/c99c43e659e24135469fc9075265adc4">Email to a friend</a></dd><dt><a href="/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=318&dockey=xml/c/9/c99c43e659e24135469fc9075265adc4&source=null&ral=JobSearch?



					op=302







					%26dockey=xml/c/9/c99c43e659e24135469fc9075265adc4" target=_top>Click Here to Apply</a></dt></dl><div class=job_description><a class=printerFriendly href=# onclick="window.open('/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=302&printView=1&force=1&dockey=xml/c/9/c99c43e659e24135469fc9075265adc4', 'PrintView', 'width=600, height=600, toolbar=0, scrollbars=1, menubar=0, location=0');">Printer-Friendly</a><h1>Job Description</h1><div class=dc_content><ul class=job_details><li class=position>Quality Engineer - Medical Mfg (Direct)</li><li class=location>georgetown, CT</li></ul> Position: <br>* High visibility role created by an internal promotion within an expanding manufacturer of innovative medical products. <br>* You will be engaged with total product evolution from development to delivery with a strong emphasis on quality input to product development and supplier support. <br>* Report to and be mentored by leadership at the director and vice president level. Participate in design projects including development of design control deliverables, risk analysis, FMEA, design verification, etc. <br>* Design gauges; review drawings to ensure GD&T, process/material specifications, and other requirements. <br>* Serve as quality engineering resource for a growing cadre of suppliers. <br>* Perform supplier audits and evaluate/set expectations for new suppliers.<br>* Implement improvements through the use of process flowcharting, pareto analysis, correlation and regression analysis, statistical process control, gauge repeatability and reproducibility, and trend analysis. Investigate and analyze internal failures and customer complaints. <br>* Review engineering change control requests. Maintain compliance with quality and regulatory standards.<br><br>Requirements<br>* BS Engineering. <br>* Seeking 5+ years of business experience with at least last 2+ years in quality engineering within a regulated industry (i.e. FDA, DCA, FAA). <br>* Should have some 3D CAD systems and a strong understanding of federal regulations and quality system standards.<br>* MBA, CQE, or CRE a plus. <br><br>NOTES: <br>* Could be a Manufacturing Engineer with Quality Engineering experience<br>* Revenue growth expectations of 30% in 2010 are expected to increase in 2011 as a result of new products and global expansion. <br>* LOCAL CANDIDATES ONLY<br>* Direct inquiries only please (no 3rd parties)<br><br>Please apply at www.bluelinetalent.com/active_jobs<br><br>Ron Levis<br>Principal<br>Blue Line Talent <br>LinkedIn: http://www.linkedin.com/in/ronlevis (invites welcome)<br><br>Blue Line Talent is a member-owner of NPA, The Worldwide Recruiting Network, your connection to premier independent recruiting firms located throughout Europe, Asia, Australia, Africa and the Americas. </div><!-- end dc_content --></div><!-- end job_description --><div class=company_overview><h1>Company Overview</h1><div class=dc_content><h2><a href="/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=308&did=10372285&cn=Blue+Line+Talent+LLC">find more jobs with this company</a></h2><div style=clear:both;></div></div></div><!-- end company_overview --><dl class=buttons><dd class=save><a id=saveJob2 href=#; title="Save Job">Save this job</a></dd><dd class=email><a href="/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=305&dockey=xml/c/9/c99c43e659e24135469fc9075265adc4&source=null&ral=JobSearch?



					op=302







