					op=302







					%26dockey=xml/6/9/698c64ac74dba479ba7398537009d572" target=_top>Click Here to Apply</a></dt></dl><div class=job_description><a class=printerFriendly href=# onclick="window.open('/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=302&printView=1&force=1&dockey=xml/6/9/698c64ac74dba479ba7398537009d572', 'PrintView', 'width=600, height=600, toolbar=0, scrollbars=1, menubar=0, location=0');">Printer-Friendly</a><h1>Job Description</h1><div class=dc_content><ul class=job_details><li class=position>Windows System Administrator</li><li class=location>Washington, DC</li></ul> Concept Solutions provides strategic, technical, and problem solving expertise to large and mid-sized businesses and government organizations. We collaborate with our clients to plan, custom design, and develop effective and secured information systems to help them improve performance, increase productivity, and achieve their business goals. Concept Solutions Earned The Washington Technology 2009 Fast 50 Ranking, and Earned a Third Consecutive Deloitte Technology Fast 500 Ranking as One of the Fastest Growing Technology Companies in North America and DC Metro Area. <br><br>Concept Solutions offers a competitive salary and a generous benefits package. This package includes: Enhanced Medical Benefits, Dental, Vision & Prescription Benefits, Vision Signature Plan (VSP), Dependent Life Insurance, Short-Term & Long-Term Disability, a 401 (K) Retirement Plan, Paid Time Off (PTO), Paid Company Holidays, Tuition Assistance Program (TAP), Employee Assistance Program (EAP) and much more. <br><br>Job Title: Windows System Administrator <br><br>Location: Washington DC (3-4 days/week) and Reston, VA<br><br>Functional Responsibility: <br>- Selects, installs, configures, and administers hardware and software systems over a LAN/WAN architecture;<br>- Installs and maintains system upgrades, operating and security patches, and peripheral devices;<br>- Supports, monitors, tests, and troubleshoots hardware and software problems related to server hardware, software, or network equipment;<br>- Recommends and schedules repairs or replacement of equipment;<br>- Provides end users support for the server and server-based applications and connectivity;<br>- Installs, configures, and manages the equipment and software necessary to perform system backups and recovery of applications and data;<br>- Maintains system and data files, and monitors system integrity;<br>- Assists technical team with system problems, troubleshoots user issues;<br>- Support SDLC plans and requirements;<br>- Support major FAA systems, network and architecture migration;<br>- Work within team providing 24/7 on-call support on a production architecture.<br><br><br>Education/Experience Requirements: <br><br>- A Bachelor*s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Mathematics, Operations Research, Statistics, Engineering, or a related field from an accredited college or university and 3 (three) years of experience performing the foregoing functions, OR a Masters Degree and 2 (two) years experience performing the foregoing functions. No college Degree would require 8 (eight) years experience;<br>- Experience in Windows Server Systems Administration and Engineering;<br>- Knowledge of FAA service contract programs, associated services and internal and external organizations that interface with the FAA is desirable.<br><br>Qualifications:<br>- Able to demonstrate mastery of the Windows Server environment;<br>- Competent in Intel/AMD-based hardware installation, maintenance and analysis;<br>- Experience in configuring and Supporting EMC- mid-range data protection architecture such as Clarion class libraries network storage architecture;<br>- Experience in supporting network/system monitoring tools such as Nagios and HP OpenView technologies;<br>- Webserver support;<br>- Preferred Certifications include MCSE;<br>- Demonstrate good writing and communication skills.<br><br>All applicants must be authorized to work in the United States, and should not require sponsorship for employment visa now or in the future. The applicant's education, skills and experience determines the level of this position.<br><br>Applicants selected will be subject to a Government security investigation (Public Trust Security Clearance) and must meet eligibility requirements for access to sensitive information. <br><br><br>Equal Opportunity Employer </div><!-- end dc_content --></div><!-- end job_description --><div class=company_overview><h1>Company Overview</h1><div class=dc_content><h2><a href="/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=308&did=RTL214196&cn=Concept+Solutions">find more jobs with this company</a></h2><div style=clear:both;></div></div></div><!-- end company_overview --><dl class=buttons><dd class=save><a id=saveJob2 href=#; title="Save Job">Save this job</a></dd><dd class=email><a href="/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=305&dockey=xml/6/9/698c64ac74dba479ba7398537009d572&source=null&ral=JobSearch?



