	  --><div id=description_col><dl class=buttons><dd class=save><a id=saveJob href=# title="Save Job">Save this job</a></dd><dd class=email><a href="/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=305&dockey=xml/1/d/1d719393cdd1c9c2a26c328f78cada4b&source=null&ral=JobSearch?



					op=302







					%26dockey=xml/1/d/1d719393cdd1c9c2a26c328f78cada4b">Email to a friend</a></dd><dt><a href="/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=318&dockey=xml/1/d/1d719393cdd1c9c2a26c328f78cada4b&source=null&ral=JobSearch?



					op=302







					%26dockey=xml/1/d/1d719393cdd1c9c2a26c328f78cada4b" target=_top>Click Here to Apply</a></dt></dl><div class=job_description><a class=printerFriendly href=# onclick="window.open('/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=302&printView=1&force=1&dockey=xml/1/d/1d719393cdd1c9c2a26c328f78cada4b', 'PrintView', 'width=600, height=600, toolbar=0, scrollbars=1, menubar=0, location=0');">Printer-Friendly</a><h1>Job Description</h1><div class=dc_content><ul class=job_details><li class=position>Sr. DBA</li><li class=location>El Segundo, CA</li></ul> A CAREER WITH THE MMOG INNOVATOR AND DEVELOPER/PUBLISHER OF LEADING FREE-TO-PLAY ONLINE GAMES.<br><br>We are Nexon America Inc., the North American publishing arm of Nexon Group (1994), a pioneer of interactive entertainment software and the world*s leader in massive multiplayer online games which it developed and introduced in 1996. <br><br>Nexon America opened for business in Los Angeles in 2005 to bring the best of online entertainment to North American audiences. The company*s growing library of titles includes the world-famous franchise MapleStory, the role playing fantasy life of Mabinogi and the online multiplayer first-person shooter Combat Arms. <br><br>Provide 24x7 supports of over 100 database servers. Install, configure, deploy and troubleshoot SQL 2008, 2005 and 2000 servers. Maintain and set up SQL Server high availability solutions like Clustering, Database mirroring, Log Shipping and Replication. Sr. DBA works closely with users to design and develop new business logic and reports in the proper context. This person must have skills that are necessary to lead the organization in successful design, implementation, and administrator of SQL Server 2000, 2005 and 2008 databases. <br><br><br>Responsibilities:<br>* Maintain and monitoring databases in 24*7 environment<br>* Assist with daily operations and support<br>* Design, develop and maintain OLTP/DW and reporting applications<br>* Ensure integrity, reliability & quality of data<br>* Analyze system and database performance, health checks and implement tuning improvements<br>* Contribute to architectural directions and new features evaluation/ implementation<br>* Guide other team members on appropriate use of database features and structures<br><br>Qualifications:<br>* 6+ years experience of support high availability production SQL server environment understanding and managing of large databases (over 1T in size)<br>* Proficiency in the following: SSIS, SSAS, SSRS, T-SQL, SQL 2005/2008, MS SQL Server, RDBMS, Cube Design, SQL coding, Query -- extensive database programming experience<br>* Hands on experience in SQL server cluster, mirroring, log shipping and replication<br>* Have excellent problem solving & analytical skill <br>* Have in-depth knowledge of DBMS Internals and performance tuning<br>* Have strong interpersonal and communication skills<br>* Ability to lead and train department employees to enhance their technical knowledge / skills<br>* Willingness to work additional hours and travel when needed<br>* Bachelor*s Degree in Computer Science preferred or equivalent combination of education and experience<br><br><br>How to Apply:<br>Qualified candidates please apply in our career page: http://www.nexon.net/Etc/Careers.aspx<br><br>Nexon America is committed to offering competitive benefits and perks including but not limited to healthcare coverage, paid holidays, year-end break, matching 401K program, Feed-Me-Tuesdays & Fridays, flexible paid time off, company-paid team outings, subsidized onsite gym membership, subsidized language courses, massage chairs, free Starbucks coffee, tea, soda fountain, discounted vending snack machines, and much more!<br><br>NOTE: To all recruitment firms: Nexon America is not accepting agency/search firm referrals for this posting, or other postings, without prior written permission from Nexon's Staffing organization. Nexon is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. <br><br>Nexon America is an Equal Opportunity Employer and welcomes diversity. </div><!-- end dc_content --></div><!-- end job_description --><div class=company_overview><h1>Company Overview</h1><div class=dc_content><h2><a href="/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=308&did=RTX145586&cn=Nexon+America">find more jobs with this company</a></h2><div style=clear:both;></div></div></div><!-- end company_overview --><dl class=buttons><dd class=save><a id=saveJob2 href=#; title="Save Job">Save this job</a></dd><dd class=email><a href="/jobsearch/servlet/JobSearch?op=305&dockey=xml/1/d/1d719393cdd1c9c2a26c328f78cada4b&source=null&ral=JobSearch?



