 width=250 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td colspan=2 valign=top><p class=header2>Job Overview </p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 valign=top class=overview_nav><table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=2><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Company:</td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks><a href="http://www.careerbuilder.com/JobSeeker/Companies/CompanyDetails.aspx?HHName=AnalystsInternationalCorporation122324" title="Click Here to Navigate To the Company Web Site">Analysts International Corporation</a></td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Base Pay: </td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks>$120,000 - $125,000 /Year</td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Other Pay:</td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks>Full benefits available.</td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Employee Type:</td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks>Full-Time</td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Industry:</td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks>Computer Software</td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Manages Others: </td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks>No</td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Job Type:</td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks>Information Technology</td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Required Education:</td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks>None</td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Required Experience:</td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks>At least 5 year(s)</td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Required Travel:</td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks>None</td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Relocation Covered:</td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks>No</td></tr><tr><td valign=top class=overview_nav>Reference ID: </td><td valign=top id=overviewlinks>86081 </td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top class=overview_nav>Location:</td><td width=50% valign=top id=overviewlinks><a id=JobDetails_ucJobDetailsSkin__JobSkinContent_ucJobLocation0_cbhlMapJob class=BingMap rel=nofollow href="#lat=33.0272,lon=-117.1176,mapsize=small,thumbnailmap=False,streetlevel=False,maptoken="><img src=http://img.icbdr.com/images/JS/jobresults/mapit.gif id=JobDetails_ucJobDetailsSkin__JobSkinContent_ucJobLocation0_imgMapIt alt="map it!">US-CA-San Diego</a><iframe id=iframeForInlineMap frameborder=0 scrolling=no style=display:none;></iframe><div id=JobDetails_ucJobDetailsSkin__JobSkinContent_ucJobLocation0_pnlLoadingMap class=loadingMap style=display:none;><img src=http://img.icbdr.com/images/js/widgets/loading.gif id=JobDetails_ucJobDetailsSkin__JobSkinContent_ucJobLocation0_imgLoadingMap class=imgLoadingMap><br> Loading Map... </div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 align=center><a id=JobDetails_ucJobDetailsSkin__JobSkinContent_ucJobMap0_cbhlMapJob class=BingMap rel=nofollow href="#lat=33.0272,lon=-117.1176,mapsize=small,thumbnailmap=True,streetlevel=False,maptoken="></a><iframe id=iframeForInlineMap frameborder=0 scrolling=no style=display:none;></iframe><div id=JobDetails_ucJobDetailsSkin__JobSkinContent_ucJobMap0_pnlLoadingMap class=loadingMap><img src=http://img.icbdr.com/images/js/widgets/loading.gif id=JobDetails_ucJobDetailsSkin__JobSkinContent_ucJobMap0_imgLoadingMap class=imgLoadingMap><br> Loading Map... </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=top class=overview_nav></td><td valign=top></td></tr><!--End Job Overview Table--><!--Begin Contact Info Table--><tr><td valign=top class=overview_nav>Contact: </td><td valign=top id=overviewlinks>Jim Schreiber </td></tr><tr><td valign=top class=overview_nav>Phone: </td><td valign=top id=overviewlinks>952-838-3059 </td></tr><tr><td valign=top class=overview_nav>Email: </td><td valign=top id=overviewlinks><a href="http://www.careerbuilder.com/JobSeeker/ApplyOnline/ApplyStart.aspx?Job_DID=J8E0T169FVRNVLTK882">Send Email Now</a></td></tr><tr><td valign=top class=overview_nav>Fax: </td><td valign=top id=overviewlinks>Not Available </td></tr><tr><td valign=top class=overview_nav></td><td valign=top id=overviewlinks></td></tr><tr><td></td></tr><tr><td></td></tr></table><!--End Contact Info Table--></td></tr><tr><td style="padding-top:30px; padding-bottom:20px;"><!--$JobSkinImage04$--></td></tr></table></td><td valign=top><table width=480 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=20><tr><td><p class=header2>Company Overview </p><p align=justify>Analysts International Corporation (AIC) is an IT services firm fully dedicated to the success and satisfaction of its customers. From IT staffing to project-based solutions, AIC provides a broad range of services designed to help businesses and government agencies drive value, control costs and deliver on the promise of a more efficient and productive enterprise. The Company offers a flexible, collaborative approach; clear industry perspective; and the breadth, scale and experience to deliver results.</p><a id=complinks href="http://www.careerbuilder.com/JobSeeker/Companies/CompanyDetails.aspx?HHName=AnalystsInternationalCorporation122324">Learn More about Analysts International Corporation</a><br><a href=http://www.analysts.com/ id=complinks>Visit Our Site</a><br><!--  <a href="#" id="complinks">Company links</a> --><br><br><br><table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td><span class=job_title>Product Manager</span></td><td align=right class=apply><a href="http://www.careerbuilder.com/JobSeeker/ApplyOnline/ApplyStart.aspx?Job_DID=J8E0T169FVRNVLTK882" onclick="CB.AskInfoBox.tallyApplyNowClick('AN05G67RWKYR5P8ZVH');" class=btnJobSkin title="Apply for this job now!">Apply Now</a><br><span id=JobDetails_ucJobDetailsSkin__JobSkinContent_ucJobFeedback_jobFeedbackWrapper style=padding-right:4px;><a id=JobDetails_ucJobDetailsSkin__JobSkinContent_ucJobFeedback_cbhlJobFeedback rel=nofollow target=_blank href="http://www.careerbuilder.com/jobseeker/accessible/jobfeedback.aspx?Job_DID=J8E0T169FVRNVLTK882">Report It</a></span></td></tr></table><p class=header>Job Description </p><div class=job_desc><div class=RichText_Content><p>&nbsp;</p><div>Product marketing Manager, Web-connect Solutions </div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>We have an exciting opening within Marketing to lead the definition and development of Web based workflow solutions, including access and printing from a series of cloud services, partners and a variety of mobile devices.  This position will be responsible for managing and driving the marketing strategy and solutions roadmap in alignment with multiple IPG organizations.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Key responsibilities</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>         Leverage Web industry experience to define strategy, manage the life cycle of SMB solutions &amp; web services for inkjet printers and multifunction devices.</div><div>         Develop roadmaps, drive implementation and market introduction.</div><div>         Drive research projects requirements to understand customer needs. Discover insights, create use cases and desired customer experiences.</div><div>         Work with R&amp;D teams to drive the definition of the product and solution portfolio</div><div>         Co-lead, with R&amp;D Program Manager, all deliverables required to advance programs through product life cycle, including the prioritization process and check points</div><div>         Drive strategic choices with VP-level management and across IPG to develop the marketing mix and new business models  </div><div>         Work with external partners to provide complete solutions and seamless workflows</div><div>         Ensure consistent implementation of solutions roadmap across the hardware portfolio</div><div>         Determine naming, positioning and messaging prior to introduction</div><div>         Work with regional partners to determine the GTM strategy and an introduction process that assures an effective worldwide launch</div><div>         Influence at the vice president and above level</div></div></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><div><div><strong>Education and Experience Required:</strong></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>•        Master's degree in Marketing/Business/Technical</div><div>•        Significant (4+ years) experience working in web-based firms focused on solutions and workflows</div><div>•        7+ years experience in product marketing fundamentals</div><div>•        3+ years experience in market analysis &amp; strategy development</div><div>•        Extensive knowledge of business printing/computing market and SMB customer needs</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><strong>Critical Competencies and Skills Required:</strong></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>•        Market analysis</div><div>•        Turning customer knowledge into actionable insights</div><div>•        Product/solution life cycle management</div><div>•        Collaborating with R&amp;D, Business Development, Supply Chain and other stake holders</div><div>•        Developing complete solutions across hardware, software and services</div><div>•        Driving strategic choices to develop the marketing mix</div><div>•        Program management skills</div><div>•        Building alignment across multiple organizations, working with global teams</div><div>•        Confident interaction with senior management</div><div>•        Managing external partners</div><div>•        Building and leading effective teams</div><div>•        Ability to make difficult decisions with good business judgment</div><div>•        Change management</div><div>•        Problem solving skills</div><div>•        Strong written and verbal communication skills</div><div>&nbsp;</div></div><div><strong>Critical Competencies to Drive Business Results:</strong></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Product/Service/Solution Roadmap Orchestration</div><div>Collaborates with business planners, R&amp;D and other stakeholders in the development of market-driven roadmaps structured to increase the profitability of the corporation</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Interactive PSS Lifecycle Marketing</div><div>Plans the interactive component of the marketing mix</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Pricing Knowledge Management</div><div>Captures and shares  business capabilities and best practices associated with pricing and business management systems</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Product Lifecycle Management</div><div>Understands and applies lifecycle methodology to accomplish work objectives</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Marketing Resources</div><div>Uses industry marketing resources expertly to access and apply relevant data or information in development or decision making</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Marketing Strategy</div><div>Understands and effectively integrates  strategic marketing direction with task-oriented goals and initiatives</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Customer Insight Marketing</div><div>Generates and applies actionable insights to build competitive advantage</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>HP Marketing Partners</div><div>Understands HP's marketing partners and their specific contribution to achieving HP's marketing goals</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Change Management</div><div>Develops methods for supporting innovation and change across the organization</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Problem Solving</div><div>Approaches problems in a rational manner using sound strategies that ensure comprehensive understanding and effective resolution</div></div></div> </div><br><br><p class=header>Job Requirements </p><div class=job_req><div class=RichText_Content><p>An Internet savvy professional who is connected in the web-industry, has experience in future product/solution marketing, identifying web-services based business opportunities that can be linked to our printing franchise.  Looking less for printer industry knowledge that we have plenty of in the company, rather complementary expertise in web-services or  software as a service (SaaS). <br> The person will manage a team of ~ 6 professionals who will define use cases/customer experiences with R&amp;D and design teams, define positioning/messaging and launch the web-based solutions (print apps, mobile apps,…) in conjunction with our printers or via separate web-releases of the apps to our installed base. </p></div> </div><p> </p><table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td></td><td align=right class=apply><a href="http://www.careerbuilder.com/JobSeeker/ApplyOnline/ApplyStart.aspx?Job_DID=J8E0T169FVRNVLTK882" onclick="CB.AskInfoBox.tallyApplyNowClick('AN05G67RWKYR5P8ZVH');" class=btnJobSkin title="Apply for this job now!">Apply Now</a><br><span id=JobDetails_ucJobDetailsSkin__JobSkinContent_ucJobFeedback_jobFeedbackWrapper style=padding-right:4px;><a id=JobDetails_ucJobDetailsSkin__JobSkinContent_ucJobFeedback_cbhlJobFeedback rel=nofollow target=_blank href="http://www.careerbuilder.com/jobseeker/accessible/jobfeedback.aspx?Job_DID=J8E0T169FVRNVLTK882">Report It</a></span></td></tr></table><br><br><div class=jd_jobprivacy style="border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); padding: 3px 3px 0px; margin-left: 10px;"><font style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; color: #000000;"><strong>CareerBuilder.com's Advice</strong></font><br><br><table id=_JobDetailsv2_tblPrivacyBox border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tbody><tr valign=top><td valign=top width=30><img src=http://img.icbdr.com/images/JS/Icons/lock.gif></td><td valign=top><span id=privacy>For your<a href="http://www.careerbuilder.com/JobSeeker/Info/Privacy.htm?sc_cmp1=js_jobdetails_privacy"> privacy and protection</a>, when applying to a job online:<br>Never give your social security number to a prospective employer, provide credit card or bank account information, or perform any sort of monetary transaction. &nbsp;<a href=/JobSeeker/Info/Privacy